Mismanagement of epidemic plunges Xi Jinping’s regime into historic crisisVincent Kolo, chinaworker.info“They are lying, we know they are lying.
The Chinese regime claimed the epidemic would peak by the first week in February, which now seems hopelessly unrealistic.
Today’s crisis shows the so-called Communist (CCP) dictatorship learned nothing from the epidemic of 17 years ago.
The hit to China’s and the global economy from these events is likely to far exceed the effects of the SARS epidemic.
Wuhan, China’s fifth largest city, is a prime example of an unsustainable bubble.